records.addlTxt: Cooperate with Kewaunee Co. Dept. of Human Services

2:31 PM Defendant Taylor Jean Travis in court.  Attorney Andrew Peter Naze in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Amanda Toonen appeared in court as a friend of the court.  Court questions if there is any request for recusal as he was involved with underlying matters prior to taking the bench.  Atty. Toonen indicates there is not a request at this time further noting that Ms. Travis does not qualify for SPD representation and requests a court appointed attorney.  Court questions Ms. Travis.  Court will appoint an attorney in this matter.  Ms. Travis is to pay $50/mo. (self pay) towards the anticipated attorney fees in this matter.  Atty. Naze requests a $2,500 signature bond with the condition that Ms. Travis cooperate with Kewaunee County Department of Human Services and any of their directives and orders.  Court orders a $2,500 signature bond with the condition that Ms. Travis cooperate with the Kewaunee County Department of Human Services.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for November 17, 2022 at 02:00 pm.
